The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning to automatically generate neural network architectures, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on deep neural networks and their structure learning, which suggests the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks for image classification tasks, indicating the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Q-learning as the reinforcement learning algorithm suggests the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and the mention of exploring the possibility of combining different types of blocks in neural networks suggests the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
